Just to summarize some of the IRC discussion (and MHO on the matter):

1. We need a microversion to opt into the new behavior since the old behavior allows non-destructive rebuild of BFV instances if the image is not changing
2. The new microversion should not require the "yes I mean it" flag and just assume that you know what you're doing if you have opted into the new behavior (i.e. always destroy the root disk in the new microversion)
3. It would be ideal if the client side of this can require a little more confirmation from interactive users. If we know the server's current image, this would be ideal:

 if new_microversion and server.image_ref == requested_image_ref:
     if args.yes_really:
         do_rebuild()
     else:
         raise UserError('Rebuilding always destroys the root disk in this version, pass --yes-really')

4. We should have a test for the old and new microversions to make sure we continue to reject image changes on the old microversion and allow non-destructive ones on the new one.

